<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Assessment Setup</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
        }

        .logo {
            width: 100px;
        }

        .user {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .username {
            margin-right: 1rem;
        }

        main {
            padding: 2rem;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .info {
            margin-top: 2rem;
            border-left: 2px solid #ddd;
            padding-left: 1rem;
        }

        .info h2 {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .info ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .info li {
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        button {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            padding: 1rem 2rem;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="logo">
            <img src="logo.png" alt="TestGorilla Logo">
        </div>
        <div class="user">
            <span class="username">Hello Ash,</span>
        </div>
    </header>
    <main>
        <h1>A few things before you start</h1>
        <p>Thank you for applying and welcome to our assessment.</p>
        <p>This assessment consists of 4 tests and 5 individual custom questions.</p>
        <p>Completing it will give you a chance to show off your skills and stand out from the crowd!</p>
        <div class="info">
            <h2>Important information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>The assessment is timed. A timer is shown per test or per question.</li>
                <li>Before each test there may be preview questions, be aware the timer for the test will have already started.</li>
                <li>1 file upload question is part of the assessment.</li>
                <li>Please allow the use of your camera/webcam and do not leave fullscreen mode. Snapshots will be taken of you periodically during the assessment. These measures are taken to ensure fairness for everyone.</li>
                <li>Turn on your speakers or headphones (to play audio).</li>
                <li>You are free to use a calculator, pen and paper.</li>
                <li>We recommend completing the assessment in one go.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
<button type="button" id="get-started" data-jobid="<%= jobId %>">Get started ></button>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>&#169; 24-01-2021</p>
    </footer>
    <script>
        const getStartedButton = document.getElementById('get-started');

        getStartedButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
 const jobId = getStartedButton.getAttribute('data-jobid');
        // Now you can use jobId as needed, for example, redirect to the assessment page with the jobId
        window.location.href = `/test/${jobId}/startExam`;        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
